SIMPLE: orpine
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: orpine
<hw>or"pine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>orpin</ets>
the genus of plants which includes orpine; -- so called from the yellow
blossoms of a common species (<ets>Sedum acre</ets>). See
<er>Orpiment</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A low plant with fleshy
leaves (<spn>Sedum telephium</spn>), having clusters of purple flowers.
It is found on dry, sandy places, and on old walls, in England, and has
become naturalized in America. Called also <altname>stonecrop</altname>,
and <altname>live-forever</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>orpin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orrach</ent>⟦br⟧
